How does it look? Like new.

How does it work? Not all that well.

Kel Tecs are known for having a break-in period. This one's been fired 100+ rounds and still has issues.

(1.) Ejects spent brass in the direction of the shooter's eyes and forehead;
(2.) Fails to extract spent brass about 1 time in 20.

If you look on-line on places like Gunbroker you'll see that they ask 300 dollars or so for these. My bet is that those have these same issues---undisclosed to the buyers.

This one is being sold as-is. For a lucky buyer with gunsmithing skills and patience this could be a good deal.

This gun is not reliable enough to carry for self defense. Shooting glasses are a necessity.

Comes with one mag, box and all paperwork.
